The paper deals with pedestrian detection using multispectral data, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves deep learning and feature fusion, which are also common in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of bounding boxes and region of interest (RoI), which are common in multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
